      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MRS BULL (7) contested a similar race to this at Muswellbrook last start and wasn't in the picture until the final stages when she flashed home to be beaten under two lengths. Yet to miss the frame in three runs over today's course and distance. Nicely drawn so gets her chance for a well-deserved win. INTERRO (9) stalked the pace then let down nicely but found the winner a shade too good last time out over this distance at Canberra. Sparingly raced filly who is rock hard fit and a serious chance in a race that lacks real depth. EXTREME MERGER (8) is back in form with a couple of recent minor placings in BM66 races over 1200m. Twice a winner at today's trip so that resurgence should continue. FAVOUR THE BOLD (6) struggled last start at Muswellbrook in stronger company. Back to a more suitable trip and drops in grade so a better run is on the cards. TURGENEV (2) caught the eye at Mudgee last time. Twice a winner here so cannot be underestimated.",
